01:16:36,400 --> 01:16:39,149
And you loved
my husband too.

1255
01:16:39,150 --> 01:16:41,357
Patrick used to talk
about you a lot

1256
01:16:41,358 --> 01:16:44,316
at the beginning,
this Maggie Patterson.

1257
01:16:44,317 --> 01:16:48,232
And then one day he stopped
talking about you and...

1258
01:16:48,233 --> 01:16:50,899
I stopped being
so jealous.

1259
01:16:50,900 --> 01:16:55,775
You were just a first love
and he forgot about you.

1260
01:16:55,776 --> 01:16:57,775
Just as John will.

1261
01:16:59,650 --> 01:17:04,525
If you love my son,
you will end this thing.

1262
01:17:05,899 --> 01:17:08,191
I desperately want
to get along with you.

1263
01:17:08,192 --> 01:17:11,107
I know that would
please John.

1264
01:17:11,108 --> 01:17:13,732
Would you approve of this
if you were John’s mother?

1265
01:17:13,733 --> 01:17:15,190
I’m not his mother.

1266
01:17:15,191 --> 01:17:17,190
You could be.

1267
01:17:17,191 --> 01:17:19,566
What about children?
You gonna deny him that?

1268
01:17:19,567 --> 01:17:21,897
Are you that
selfish?

1269
01:17:21,898 --> 01:17:23,773
I want John to have
whatever he wants.

1270
01:17:23,774 --> 01:17:26,939
He’s a man.
He’s not a little boy.

1271
01:17:26,940 --> 01:17:29,524
He’s capable of making up
his own mind.

1272
01:17:29,525 --> 01:17:31,689
Are you so angry

1273
01:17:31,690 --> 01:17:34,105
because Patrick didn’t
return your letter?

1274
01:17:34,106 --> 01:17:37,730
Why don’t you admit that you
had to have a piece of Patrick

1275
01:17:37,731 --> 01:17:40,688
because you couldn’t
have him before?

1276
01:17:40,689 --> 01:17:44,648
He forgot about you
and turned to me.

1277
01:17:44,649 --> 01:17:50,606
And you are using John
and that is cruel.

1278
01:17:50,607 --> 01:17:52,897
Even if Patrick
hadn’t existed,

1279
01:17:52,898 --> 01:17:55,439
I’d feel the same way
about John.

1280
01:17:57,649 --> 01:17:58,897
I want to give him
something.

1281
01:18:00,023 --> 01:18:02,856
If you really
love John,

1282
01:18:02,857 --> 01:18:05,813
then you will
leave him alone.

1283
01:18:05,814 --> 01:18:07,897
What kind of a future
would he have with you?

1284
01:18:23,189 --> 01:18:26,063
MAN: Get him up there. Yeah!
Yes!

1285
01:18:32,690 --> 01:18:34,689
[PHONE RINGS]

1286
01:19:06,604 --> 01:19:09,189
You should be
celebrating with me.

1287
01:19:13,520 --> 01:19:17,562
The perceptive part of me
is guessing you’re not out here,

1288
01:19:17,563 --> 01:19:19,604
pondering my
game-winning goal.

1289
01:19:20,811 --> 01:19:22,770
I have some things
to say to you.

1290
01:19:22,771 --> 01:19:26,519
My mother was way
out of line, okay?

1291
01:19:26,520 --> 01:19:28,935
We had it out.
She went home.

1292
01:19:28,936 --> 01:19:32,560
What we have
isn’t right.

1293
01:19:32,561 --> 01:19:34,810
All of this because
of what my mother said?

1294
01:19:34,811 --> 01:19:37,645
Don’t you understand?
I don’t care what she thinks.

1295
01:19:37,646 --> 01:19:39,101
What anybody thinks.

1296
01:19:39,102 --> 01:19:40,936
John, there’s
someone else.

1297
01:19:42,978 --> 01:19:45,226
Your father.

1298
01:19:45,227 --> 01:19:48,770
I came back here
to find him again.

1299
01:19:48,771 --> 01:19:50,977
And he was dead.

1300
01:19:52,853 --> 01:19:55,104
And there you were.

1301
01:19:57,227 --> 01:20:01,477
And I took you like
a wonderful confection.

1302
01:20:01,478 --> 01:20:03,019
What are you
talking about?

1303
01:20:03,020 --> 01:20:05,643
I substituted
you.

1304
01:20:05,644 --> 01:20:09,601
That’s what it was.
Um, it’s mistaken identity.

1305
01:20:09,602 --> 01:20:10,893
I don’t believe
that.

1306
01:20:10,894 --> 01:20:12,977
Well,
that is what it is.

1307
01:20:15,643 --> 01:20:17,477
And you deserve
more.

1308
01:20:30,644 --> 01:20:32,727
Can I hold you?

1309
01:21:19,433 --> 01:21:20,850
Goodbye, Maggie.

1310
01:21:31,432 --> 01:21:33,434
[CAR DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

1311
01:21:36,932 --> 01:21:38,974
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

1312
01:21:45,183 --> 01:21:47,183
[♪♪♪]

1313
01:21:50,265 --> 01:21:52,641
[CLICKING]

1314
01:22:13,348 --> 01:22:15,307
Hi, babe.
Hi.

1315
01:22:15,308 --> 01:22:16,930
Don’t have any
pictures of you.

1316
01:22:16,931 --> 01:22:19,098
CLAIRE:
No. No pictures. Down.

1317
01:22:19,099 --> 01:22:21,849
I have burned every
single one after 40.

1318
01:22:23,097 --> 01:22:24,639
[CLICKING]

1319
01:22:24,640 --> 01:22:28,473
Bitch. Why do I even want
to be your partner?

1320
01:22:28,474 --> 01:22:33,096
Oh, you’re gonna have to sign
these papers before you leave.

1321
01:22:33,097 --> 01:22:36,513
Oh, I finally get
my old friend back

1322
01:22:36,514 --> 01:22:39,514
and you, you change
your mind and take off.

1323
01:22:39,515 --> 01:22:42,514
Why are you
running away again?

1324
01:22:42,515 --> 01:22:44,555
The whole summer
I’ve let you pound me,

1325
01:22:44,556 --> 01:22:47,180
analyze me, tell me
what’s best for me.

1326
01:22:47,181 --> 01:22:49,014
You don’t know
what’s best for me.

1327
01:22:49,015 --> 01:22:50,679
Nobody does.

1328
01:22:50,680 --> 01:22:52,222
First Patrick.
Hmm?

1329
01:22:52,223 --> 01:22:54,263
And now you’re running away
from John.

1330
01:22:54,264 --> 01:22:56,555
Enough!
John is a gift.

1331
01:22:56,556 --> 01:22:57,971
Don’t throw
it away.

1332
01:22:57,972 --> 01:23:00,513
It’s none
of your business.

1333
01:23:04,097 --> 01:23:06,679
I’m sorry.

1334
01:23:06,680 --> 01:23:08,638
Now you just shut up.

1335
01:23:10,806 --> 01:23:13,180
[SIGHS]

1336
01:23:15,972 --> 01:23:18,136
You take care of
this place.

1337
01:23:18,137 --> 01:23:21,762
I’m a silent partner,
but I can complain.

1338
01:23:23,971 --> 01:23:25,513
At the soccer game,

1339
01:23:25,514 --> 01:23:27,345
when you told me
about you and John,

1340
01:23:27,346 --> 01:23:29,261
I was scared for you,
Maggie,

1341
01:23:29,262 --> 01:23:31,220
because I thought
you’d get hurt.

1342
01:23:31,221 --> 01:23:35,179
That it was just
a sexual thing for him.

1343
01:23:35,180 --> 01:23:37,262
But today I stopped
by his place

1344
01:23:37,263 --> 01:23:41,304
and the way he talks about you,
he does love you.

1345
01:23:41,305 --> 01:23:42,844
I know.

1346
01:23:42,845 --> 01:23:44,096
What are you
afraid of?

1347
01:23:47,137 --> 01:23:49,679
I’m afraid he’ll never
know where he stands.

1348
01:23:49,680 --> 01:23:51,345
As much as
you love him?

1349
01:23:51,346 --> 01:23:54,760
Come on. Look, no one
has a crystal ball.

1350
01:23:54,761 --> 01:23:56,802
Take the risk.

1351
01:23:56,803 --> 01:23:59,136
It’s worth it.

1352
01:23:59,137 --> 01:24:00,927
I’m doing what’s
best for him.

1353
01:24:00,928 --> 01:24:02,595
And best for me.

1354
01:24:02,596 --> 01:24:04,511
No. I, uh...

1355
01:24:05,970 --> 01:24:08,595
He gave me this
for you.

1356
01:24:16,636 --> 01:24:20,511
MAGGIE:
Patrick, where are you?

1357
01:24:20,512 --> 01:24:22,803
I’ve come
to say goodbye.

1358
01:24:25,095 --> 01:24:27,219
Couldn’t do it
before.

1359
01:24:39,761 --> 01:24:42,260
"Maggie, I found this
in my father’s belongings.

1360
01:24:42,261 --> 01:24:44,219
He never mailed it."

1361
01:24:59,677 --> 01:25:03,175
"Dear Maggie.
I was saddened by your letter

1362
01:25:03,176 --> 01:25:05,424
"and what you’ve been
going through.

1363
01:25:05,425 --> 01:25:09,009
"The loss of your mother,
your father’s illness,

1364
01:25:09,010 --> 01:25:12,801
"that you wouldn’t be back
to The Moon this summer.

1365
01:25:12,802 --> 01:25:15,217
"When I called to talk to you,
your father told me

1366
01:25:15,218 --> 01:25:17,507
"that the real reason
you weren’t coming back

1367
01:25:17,508 --> 01:25:21,801
"was because you had
met another guy.

1368
01:25:24,843 --> 01:25:27,467
"That you couldn’t
tell me.

1369
01:25:31,426 --> 01:25:34,675
"He asked me
not to write to you.

1370
01:25:39,093 --> 01:25:43,257
"All right, dear, Maggie.
I wish you joy and what else?

1371
01:25:43,258 --> 01:25:48,091
"And whatever happens
to you or me,

1372
01:25:48,092 --> 01:25:49,759
"remember,

1373
01:25:51,175 --> 01:25:54,340
"we’ve got to live lives

1374
01:25:54,341 --> 01:25:59,008
"fully and unafraid,

1375
01:26:01,216 --> 01:26:03,967
"like we pledged
to each other.

1376
01:26:08,216 --> 01:26:10,216
Love, Patrick."

1377
01:26:44,423 --> 01:26:46,299
Can I
join you?

1378
01:26:59,673 --> 01:27:01,839
I just want to
be with you.

1379
01:27:37,212 --> 01:27:39,755
[♪♪♪]

